Title : Jan Mans
Text : [[File:JanMans20040914.jpg|thumb|Jan Mans in front of the Enschede synagogue in 2004]]
'''J.H.H. (Jan) Mans''' (born 9 April 1940 in [[Heerlen]]) is a Dutch politician of the [[Labour Party (Netherlands)|Labour Party]] (PvdA).

Mans studied [[sociology]] at [[Radboud University Nijmegen]]. In 1982 he was named mayor of [[Meerssen]].<ref name=Meerssenform /> Six years later, in 1988 he became mayor in [[Kerkrade]].<ref name=Kerkrade />

From 1994 until 2005 he was mayor of [[Enschede]], where he was confronted with the [[Enschede fireworks disaster]] of 13 May 2000, which killed 23 people and left hundreds homeless. A report by the commission Oosting found the city government lacking in its inspections of the site before the accident. The mayors actions during the disaster found general support and he remained in office for another five years.<ref name=Meerssenform /><ref>[http://krant.telegraaf.nl/krant/focus/vuurwerk/teksten/vuurwerk.manswachtaf.html Burgemeester Mans wacht oordeel gemeenteraad af], [[De Telegraaf]], 1 March 2001</ref><ref name=Moerdijk /><ref name=Gouda />

In May 2005 he left Enschede and was asked to be acting mayor of [[Venlo]]. In October 2005 he became acting mayor of [[Zaanstad]] until April 2006. Since 1 December 2006 he is chairman of the [[Chamber of commerce]] of Northern and Southern [[Limburg (Netherlands)|Limburg]]. On 14 January 2010 he became acting mayor of [[Maastricht]],<ref name=Kerkrade>[http://www.rtlnieuws.nl/nieuws/binnenland/jan-mans-tijdelijk-opvolger-leers Jan Mans tijdelijk opvolger Leers], [[RTL Nieuws]], 14 January 2010</ref><ref name=Moerdijk /><ref name=Gouda /><ref name=Maastricht>[http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/2686/Binnenland/archief/article/detail/977069/2010/01/15/Jan-Mans-waarnemend-burgemeester-Maastricht-college-blijft-aan.dhtml Jan Mans waarnemend burgemeester Maastricht, college blijft aan], [[Volkskrant]], 15 January 2010</ref> and on 1 February 2011 he became acting mayor of Moerdijk, replacing [[Wim Denie]] who retired early after a fire at Chemie-Pack.<ref name=Moerdijk>[http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/2686/Binnenland/article/detail/1825741/2011/01/18/Jan-Mans-waarnemend-burgemeester-in-Moerdijk.dhtml Jan Mans waarnemend burgemeester in Moerdijk], [[Volkskrant]], 18 January 2011</ref><ref name=Gouda /> In 2012 Mans was acting mayor of [[Gouda, South Holland|Gouda]] succeeding [[Wim Cornelis]], who retired early.<ref name=Gouda>[http://www.telegraaf.nl/binnenland/20054731/__Mans_tijdelijk_burgemeester_van_Gouda__.html Mans tijdelijk burgemeester van Gouda], [[De Telegraaf]], 16 May 2012</ref>

In April 2013, he led the talks to form a new coalition in the city council of [[Meerssen]], after the fall of the local coalition.<ref name=Meerssenform>[http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/2844/Archief/archief/article/detail/3428167/2013/04/19/Jan-Mans-formateur-in-Meerssen.dhtml Jan Mans formateur in Meerssen], [[Volkskrant]], 19 April 2013</ref>

